 chapter on homeward trends points out some of the challenges that Article 80 poses to international uniformity. Extensive comparisons to UPICC and PECL are carried out. The book is relevant to scholars, adjudicators and practitioners alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aExport sales contracts. 0aUnited Nations Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods -- (1980). 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist History 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062100608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE LAW  2012z978311029381408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET RECHTSWISSENSCHAFTEN 2012z9783110288919oZDB-23-DGC40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978386653962440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783866539624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783866539624/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-029381-4  E-BOOK PACKAGE LAW  2012b2012  a978-3-11-062100-6  DGBA Backlist History 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GLAc2000d2014